# =============================================================================
# ADMIN PANEL ENV CONFIGURATION
# =============================================================================
#
# This admin panel uses VITE (React), NOT Next.js!
#
# ✅ CORRECT PREFIX: VITE_
#    - Use: VITE_API_BASE_URL=https://your-backend.onrender.com
#    - Vercel/build tools WILL expose variables with VITE_ prefix to the client
#
# =============================================================================

# API BACKEND CONFIGURATION
# -------------------------
# 
# The admin panel now accepts any HTTPS backend URL (not limited to Render).
# See admin-panel/src/lib/apiUrl.ts for implementation details.
#
# Environment variable priority:
# 1. VITE_API_BASE_URL (preferred)
# 2. VITE_API_URL (fallback for compatibility)
# 3. Same-origin (window.location.origin) - for Vercel proxy setups
# 4. Default: https://hiremebahamas-backend.onrender.com
#
# FOR LOCAL DEVELOPMENT (HTTP acceptable for localhost only):
# ✅ Set VITE_API_BASE_URL or VITE_API_URL to local backend
# ✅ Example: VITE_API_BASE_URL=http://localhost:8000
#
# FOR PRODUCTION:
# ✅ Set VITE_API_BASE_URL to your backend URL
# ✅ Example: VITE_API_BASE_URL=https://hiremebahamas-backend.onrender.com
# ✅ HTTPS is required (HTTP only allowed for localhost)
# ✅ Any HTTPS host is now accepted
#
# FOR VERCEL DEPLOYMENTS WITH PROXY:
# ✅ Leave env vars unset to use same-origin fallback
# ✅ API calls will go to your Vercel domain via proxy
#
# Uncomment and set for local development:
# VITE_API_BASE_URL=http://localhost:8000
# Or use legacy variable (still supported):
# VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:8000

# =============================================================================
# DEPLOYMENT NOTES
# =============================================================================
#
# For Vercel deployments:
# 1. Set VITE_API_BASE_URL in Vercel Dashboard → Settings → Environment Variables
# 2. Use HTTPS URLs only (e.g., VITE_API_BASE_URL=https://your-backend.onrender.com)
#
# For local development:
# 1. Copy this file: cp .env.example .env
# 2. Set VITE_API_BASE_URL=http://localhost:8000 (HTTP acceptable for localhost only)
# 3. Start backend: cd ../backend && python -m uvicorn app.main:app --reload
# 4. Start admin panel: npm run dev
#
# =============================================================================
